title: Welcome aboard!
content:
We’re excited to have you join our community of rental entrepreneurs. Whether you’re brand new or already hosting, you’re in the right place to level up, connect with others, and grow your business.

Here’s how to get started:

1. Introduce YourselfPost a short intro and share your story with the group. Your background, goals, or why you joined—this helps us get to know you and keeps the energy strong!

2. Start the TrainingJump into the training videos right away. You’ll learn actionable strategies, insider tips, and proven systems to succeed with rental arbitrage—whether you’re working toward your first unit or scaling a portfolio.

3. Share and Contribute. Got a win? A tip? A lesson learned? Share it! Every post helps someone else—and the more you engage, the more you unlock (yes, we’ve got levels and badges 🔓).

4. Stuck on something? Ask. This community is built on support and collaboration, not ego. You’ll get help fast—from peers, mentors, and our team.

We’re here to help you launch, grow, and thrive in rental arbitrage—and we’re pumped to have you on the journey.

Let’s go! 🚀

title: BOIR Rules for Small Businesses
content:
On March 2, 2025, the U.S. Treasury announced it would suspend penalties and enforcement of the BOIR rules for domestic companies

In other words: Domestic entities (like your typical U.S.-based LLC or corporation) are currently exempt from filing BOIs.
